### Support Tickets API — Sample Requests
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client and JetBrains HTTP Client

@base = http://localhost:3000
@ticketId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create ticket (full valid body)
POST {{base}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-1001",
  "customer_email": "alice@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Alice Example",
  "subject": "Cannot log in to my account",
  "description": "I have been locked out of my account since yesterday. I tried resetting my password but did not receive the email.",
  "category": "account_access",
  "priority": "high",
  "status": "new",
  "assigned_to": "agent-1",
  "tags": ["login", "urgent", "password"],
  "metadata": {
    "source": "web_form",
    "browser": "Chrome 120",
    "device_type": "desktop"
  }
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# List
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all tickets
GET {{base}}/tickets

###

### Filter by status=new
GET {{base}}/tickets?status=new

###

### Filter by category=account_access
GET {{base}}/tickets?category=account_access

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get / Update / Delete by ID
# Set @ticketId to a real UUID returned from POST /tickets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get ticket by ID
GET {{base}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

###

### Partial update — change status only
PUT {{base}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### Delete ticket
DELETE {{base}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Import
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Import CSV (multipart/form-data)
# Send a CSV file using the REST Client file reference syntax.
# In VS Code REST Client: use @file = path/to/sample_tickets.csv
# In curl: curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/tickets/import -F "file=@demo/sample_tickets.csv"
POST {{base}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< ./sample_tickets.csv
------FormBoundary--

###

### Import JSON (multipart/form-data)
POST {{base}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.json"
Content-Type: application/json

< ./sample_tickets.json
------FormBoundary--

###

### Import XML (multipart/form-data)
POST {{base}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.xml"
Content-Type: application/xml

< ./sample_tickets.xml
------FormBoundary--

###
